"My Christmas present to myself! Poured from bottle into pint glass, with minimal head notwithstanding intentional efforts to render big foam with an aggressive pour (perhaps I served it too cold). Lots of tiny mocha bubbles in deep, dark background. The view is like looking into an inviting black hole, enticing the viewer to leap into the abyss. The smell is off the charts, like the love you lost in college. And that first taste reminds me of my first hint of eroticism...mystical and captivating, yielding pangs of guilty pleasure (somehow, I know what I am about to do must be illegal). The coffee flavors are almost too intense and overpowering, but not quite. Toffee, vanilla, espresso, and caramel all appear here. And the finish is so silky smooth and sweet that I didn't realize the entire experience was over, until it was. Alas, BCBCS will tease and intrigue forever, and I shall continue touts for her now more than ever. One taste is both my original sin and my eternal condemnation..."
