"Poured from a bottle into a snifter, the beer is a jet black coloring, oily consistency, with a light tan colored head, thin and filmy. Aromas of earth, oak, booze, vanilla, molasses, chocolate, roast and hints of char. Very rich and robust nose. Flavors of booze forward, with a heavy bourbon/vanilla rich and sweet follow, rich molasses and roast caramel blend in the backbone, bitter and roasted coffee notes, and some oaky/earthy notes. Amazingly and delicately balanced on a rich, smooth, dense body. The aftertaste is boozy, with a rich vanilla and coffee blend giving sweet and bitter characteristics. Smooth, creamy finish, with a bittersweet linger. Amazingly drinkable, but the warmth and booze builds quickly. This is tasty!"
