"22oz bottle with a Bottled On Date of 11/12/12. 14.3 ABV according to the bottle. Pours a pitch black color with an inch of thick, brown head. The aroma is a big whiff of booze along with roasted malts, chocolate and vanilla. Not noticing much coffee. The taste is bourbon upfront followed by the coffee. Sweet and boozey but not cloyingly sweet. Vanilla and coffee towards the end. Warming alcohol finish. Honestly, there isn't a huge difference between this one and the regular Bourbon County. You can taste some coffee but there isn't a whole lot. Heavy mouthfeel. $20 for 1 bottle compared to $24 for a 4 pack of Bourbon County makes this a one time buy; maybe pick up a second for the right price to age. Overall, its a damn fine beer but just isn't a major change from the Bourbon County."
