"Pours a dark near black, coating the class with sticky brown liquid, hard pour brings a cap of dense brown froth, gone quickly. Scent kicks off with a cup of dark roasted coffee, more brewed than bean, solid notes of vanilla combine with semi sweet baking chocolate, solid notes of whiskey and bourbon, some oak, coconut and dark fruit to boot, nicely layered scent but needs to be a bit more aggressive. Taste brings an initial hit of vanilla, sugar and cream before the dark roasted coffee and semi-sweet chocolate hit, strong whiskey and bourbon notes almost take over the palate, but beer smooths into a well layered and blended drink with additional notes of dark fruit, oak and coconut. Full bodied, not as dense despite the stickyness of the beer, lingering sweetness and booze. Overall, quite impressed with the well layered and blended notes, quie concerned that drinking so fresh would cause the bourbon to overpower, but that wasnt the case."
