"wow. pours black as can be with a barely-there coffee-with-cream colored head that disappears right away. aromas hit the olfactory before i'm even done pouring the first glass. right away, i am reminded of the best, most rich, bourbon laced chocolate cake ever. scents of deep, rich chocolate, batter, chocolate icing, bourbon, vanilla, real coffee, almonds, dark fruit, oak and more waft through the air. intensely complex. in the taste (as well as the nose actually) the flavors of bourbon and coffee are integrated extremely well, coming off as one huge, new, multi-layered taste rather than a hundred things at once. big bourbon, chocolate, vanilla flavors. the coffee seems to fit right in, and the bitterness it provides amplifies just right. full, full body with a hot finish that for once, isn't unpleasantly hot. only down side to this one is that it is so big, it is hard for me to drink more than 6 ounces or so. it is so flavorful, it seems enticing to overindulge, but the heat and richness gets me. one of the best big beers i've ever had. goose island kills it with this one."
