"Pours a jet black with thin tan head. Lacing is pretty minimal for such a big beer. Smell is a great mix of bourbon, coffee, oak and chocolate. Flavor is heavy on the coffee up front, but the bourbon comes on towards the end and combines very nicely with chocolate and oak. It's not nearly as sweet as the regular BCBS. As it warms up the coffee mellows out and blends in with the other flavors better. Mouthfeel is pretty full-bodied and a little bit sticky. Overall, this is a great Bourbon County variant, but I prefer the regular BCBS better. The coffee adds a little bit of acidity to it that disrupts the bourbon/chocolate/oak flavor I love so much."
