"Wow. What a brew. Being a relative novice in the craft beer scene (1.2 years and counting) I sometimes miss certain elements of the beer or don't consider other factors, such as mouthfeel, to be as important because I lack the perception. Well, after drinking this brew, I can say I now know the feeling of a great mouthfeel. I have had bc vanilla, bc regular 11', king henry and now this. Bourbon county coffee blows them all away. The nose is rich with bourbon sweetness, a little heat and some subtle coffee and vanilla notes. I am not blown away by booze from the nose which invites me to take a sip. Now, solely comparing the three I have tried, this is by far the best. Smooth as silk, coats the mouth like the vanilla did, but with a wonderful complexity and relatively easy drinkability. the taste rapidly changes almost as it warms each degree. I get smooth bourbon, nice subtle blend of coffee and chocolate. it is not cloying, rather smooth and luscious. When I swirl it in my mouth, huge coffee notes are unleashed at a ferocious rate. It is big, undoubtedly, but it is everything I could have ever hoped for in a bourbon county. Smooth, drinkable, great mouthfeel and a whole lot of flavor"
