"The appearance is abyssal black and pours super thick, there is absolutely no head on this beer what so ever, but it finds a way to make me forget about that pretty fast because once I smelled it god-damn was that wonderful. The aromatics off of the beer were the obvious notes of coffee and sweet bourbon, but even beyond that there was a candy like sugar smell and rich sweet milk chocolate aroma on the nose. One of my top beer smells ever. The aromatics amplified my enjoyment of the taste as well. The flavors were of a bourbon dark chocolate syrup to the point were I might consider this a dessert beer. The coffee is smooth and dosen't add really any bittering notes to beer what-so-ever. For something with dark chocolate, bourbon and coffee beans that is considered able to age for up to 5 years, this is smooth as heck right now. If it wasn't for the high ABV, I would have no problem drinking this all day long. Overall it was a great beer one of the best I've ever had the good fortune of trying."
