"I get it's not the most exciting thing to read in a review initially, but when you think about this style and how much is going on you will soon realize how impressive of a feat that is. The smell is the only thing I scored under 4.5 mostly because I was hoping for a bit of a stronger coffee aroma. I smelled the sweetness of the aged bourbon more than the coffee especially as it warmed. This isn't necessarily a bad thing and still warranted a 4.0 because it smells amazing. When I finally decided it was time to taste this beer I was overwhelmed by what was going on. You get a great coffee note up front. This blends its way into an almost vanilla like bourbon sweetness. The back end is where the barrel really shines and you can taste the bourbon and wood with some lingering coffee taste still peeking though. It's definetly not as strong of a coffee flavor as one might think. Get your hands on a bottle and please drink it fresh! I see far to many year old reviews of this beer where people talk about its lack of coffee... this isn't something to age unless you have had it fresh once and want to see what it turns into."
