"Bourbon County Brand Coffee Stout pours total black. Nigel Tufnel might say that it could be none more black. Three fingers of mocha foam rise up to crown the beer. Head retention is very good, but lacing is pretty much nonexistent. The nose is absolutely fantastic, I don't think I could ask for anything more. Rich milk chocolate, fresh brewed coffee, and smooth bourbon each jump out of the glass, no aroma dominating, but all of them quite pungent. The flavor doesn't quite live up the expectations set by the out of this world aroma. The milk chocolate aspect of the beer appears at the open, but fades quickly. That leaves the coffee, and a bourbon flavor that has a bit more bite than the nose would have led me to expect. The body is very full, with a perfectly subtle carbonation. The mouthfeel just doesn't have that creamy edge that would have completed the picture though. Almost two years later I'm impressed by how much coffee presence is left in Bourbon County Coffee Stout, and I'm looking forward to the next batch of this excellent bourbon barrel aged stout."
